This is a 2D side-scrolling action RPG prototype (MapleStory-inspired).

ARCHITECTURE
- Files in src/ organized by role: config/ core/ entities/ systems/
- All tunable values: src/config/Constants.js
- All item definitions: src/config/Items.js
- All map definitions: src/config/Maps.js
- Skill tree: src/config/SkillTree.js
- Use ES modules (import/export), not CommonJS
- No file > ~400 lines; split if larger

WORKFLOW FOR PHASE 3
- Read HANDOFF/PHASE3_HANDOFF.md before architectural decisions
- 10 files listed as "already written" in the handoff doc are FROZEN — do not modify them
- 9 files listed as "need to update" are the scope of your work
- Do updates in the order specified in the handoff doc

CODE STYLE
- Preserve existing behavior when modifying a file unless explicitly changing it
- Comment the "why", not the "what"
- Keep functions small and single-purpose
- No premature optimization

GAME DESIGN
- Game feel > graphics
- Hitstop, knockback, screen shake, and damage numbers are essential and must remain
- Fast responsive controls — no floaty movement
- Snappy audio feedback on every action
- Respawning enemies = grind never stops

TESTING
- Don't break Phase 2 save files; handle missing fields gracefully
- After each file update, verify the file passes `node --check`
- After batch updates, run the testing checklist at the bottom of the handoff doc
